    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season generously on both sides with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>black olives </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> and<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong></p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Once the steaks are cooked, transfer to a plate to rest, and keep the tomatoes in the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta<strong> </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to the pasta and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the steak is resting, return the pan to a medium heat and add your<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of olive oil if your pan is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>halved olives</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>soy sauce</strong> and a splash of the <strong>reserved pasta water</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>pizzaiola sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>to the pizzaiola sauce and cook for 1 min further or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>pasta pizzaiola</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak[s]</strong> finely on a clean board</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/seared-rump-steak-with-wholewheat-spaghetti-pizzaiola/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pasta pizzaiola</strong>, topped with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and the<strong> sliced steak</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> salad</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
